Desktop migration-history reset — approved, one-time.

Why this exists
---------------
The desktop local database engine moved from PGlite (Postgres dialect, the
`agent-dashboard.pgdata` directory) to libSQL/SQLite (a single
`agent-dashboard.sqlite` file). This is a different storage engine on a new
on-disk file, so the legacy Postgres incremental migration history cannot be
"continued" in SQLite dialect. The 14 Postgres `migration.sql` files were
removed and replaced by a single genesis SQLite migration, `0001_init`.

No SQLite desktop migration has ever shipped, so there is no immutable SQLite
checksum history in the wild to preserve — the reset is safe and intentional.

Effect on the immutability guard
--------------------------------
The `migration-immutability` job (.github/workflows/pr-test.yml) treats any
modified/deleted/renamed `migration.sql` as a violation. The presence of THIS
marker file (added in the same PR) approves the desktop deletions for the
PGlite→SQLite cutover ONLY. The cloud `packages/database` migrations remain
strictly immutable, and future desktop migrations remain immutable too: a later
edit/delete/rename does not add this marker, so it is still rejected.

Do not edit or re-add this marker to excuse a future migration change — add a
new forward migration instead (see apps/desktop/AGENTS.md).
